The South African Defence Force (SANDF) only received a formal request for assistance this morning. The country s last line of defence is currently working with Western Cape Disaster Management Centre.This followed allegations from various quarters this morning that the defence force had been reluctant to help and needed two days to prepare for the emergency operation in Knysna.Spokesperson for SANDF Siphiwe Dlamini told The Citizen that they only received the request this morning at 1am.Dlamini emphasised that the defence force had to be deployed to assist in emergency responses. We are part of Western Cape provincial joint operations centre, and everything we do is in partnership with other structures in the province, he said.Dlamini said this morning s request included water-bombing, ground troops to assist the police to prevent criminal elements taking advantage of the evacuated areas and water bunkers to ensure fire engines do not travel long distances . Caxton News ServiceRead original story on citizen.co.za